Privacy Policy for FGV Attendance Solution

1. Introduction
We are committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, store, and safeguard your data when using [Your App Name], specifically related to the use of the camera and face recognition features.

2. Data Collection
Camera Usage
Our app uses the deviceâ€™s camera to capture your face photo, which is used for our face recognition attendance feature. The camera permission (android.permission.CAMERA) is requested to enable this functionality.

Face Photo Collection
We collect your face photo when you use the face recognition feature of our app. The photo is converted into a mathematical format known as an "image encoding," which is used for later recognition.

3. Data Usage
Your face photo and its encoded version are used solely for recognizing your face during attendance verification. The data is processed using machine learning models, including ML Vision, for this purpose.

4. Data Storage and Security
All collected data, including face photos and encoded data, are securely stored in our database. We use industry-standard encryption and security measures to ensure that your data is protected from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.

5. Data Sharing
We do not share your face data or any other personal information with any third-party organizations, individuals, or external services.

6. User Rights
You have the right to delete your face data at any time. If you wish to remove your face data from our system, you can contact us at [support@example.com] or use the in-app option to delete your face image.

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated to users through updates in the app or on our website.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data rights, please contact us at kh.isaac@gmail.com.
